<article id="post-105" class="post-105 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized entry">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://blakemanproperties.com/2022/02/24/what-is-cryptocurrency-heres-what-you-need-to-know/" rel="bookmark">What is Cryptocurrency?  Here&#8217;s What You Need to Know</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	<div class="entry-content">
		
<p>Cryptocurrency is a type of digital currency that you can use to buy goods and services.  For secure transactions, cryptocurrencies rely on a more complex online ledger.  Millions of people from all over the world are investing in these unregulated currencies to make a profit.  Of all these popular cryptocurrencies, Bitcoin is at the top of the list.  In this article, we take a deeper look at cryptocurrency.  Read on to find out more.</p>
<p><b>1. What is Cryptocurrency? </b></p>
<p>Basically, you can pay through cryptocurrency to buy goods or services on the internet.  Today, many companies are releasing their own cryptocurrency.  Known tokens, they can be sold for goods and services.  You can think of these as casino chips or arcade tokens.  You can use your real money to buy cryptocurrency to make these transactions.</p>
<p>For transaction verification, cryptocurrencies use a state-of-the-art system known as blockchain.  This decentralized technology is powered by multiple computers programmed to manage and record transactions.  Security is the most important thing about this technology.</p>
<p><b>2. What is the Value of Cryptocurrency? </b></p>
<p>Today, there are over 10,000 types of cryptocurrency available out there.  And they are sold all over the world, according to reports from CoinMarketCap.  Currently, the value of all cryptocurrencies is above 1.3 trillion dollars.</p>
<p>At the top of the list is Bitcoin.  The value of all Bitcoins is $ 599.6 billion, give or take.</p>
<p><b>3. Why are they so Popular? </b></p>
<p>Cryptocurrencies have a good appeal for many reasons.  Listed below are some of the most common:</p>
<p>Some people think that cryptocurrency is the money of the future.  Therefore, many of them invest their hard earned money in the hope that the cryptocurrency will rise in value after a few years.</p>
<p>Some people think that this money can be free from central bank regulations because these institutions carry the amount of money through inflation.</p>
<p>Other supporters have chosen the technology that drives cryptocurrencies, which is the blockchain.  Basically, it is a decentralized recording and processing system, which can provide a higher level of security than conventional payment systems.</p>
<p>Some speculators go for cryptocurrency simply because it adds value.</p>
<p><b>4. Is it a Good Investment? </b></p>
<p>According to most experts, the value of cryptocurrencies will continue to rise over time.  However, some experts suggest that these are just speculations.  Like real money, this type of money has no cash flow.  So, if you want to make a profit, someone has to pay a higher amount of money to buy the money.</p>
<p>Unlike a well -managed business that increases in value over time, cryptocurrency has no assets.  But if a cryptocurrency stays strong over a long period of time, it will definitely help you earn a lot of profit.</p>
<p>In short, this is a basic introduction to cryptocurrency.  Hopefully, this article will help you familiarize yourself with this new type of money.</p>

	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

